    "creation_date" : 1582293741,
    "answer_id" : 60340175,
    "question_id" : 41617042,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Answer is: <strong>this@ActivityName</strong></p>\n<p>For example: You should use it if you would like to define &quot;Context&quot; in MainActivity.kt</p>\n<pre><code>var mContext:Context = this@MainActivity\n</code></pre>\n<p>Why? Because in Kotlin language @ has mean &quot;of&quot; such as:</p>\n<pre><code>val a = this@A // A's this\n</code></pre>\n<p>If you want to learn more information, you can look Kotlin Language website:\n<a href=\"https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/this-expressions.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">This Expression in Kotlin</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7314469,
      "reputation" : 410,
      "user_id" : 5572603,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b7e362677b708f4dacfb78ff14eb0fb5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Brian Mutiso",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5572603/brian-mutiso"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1625077260,
    "creation_date" : 1625077260,
    "answer_id" : 68199855,
    "question_id" : 41617042,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In kotlin</p>\n<pre><code>this@MainActivity\n</code></pre>\n<p>is equivalent to JAVA</p>\n<pre><code>MainActivity.this\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
